article.headline: Vermont 89, Yale 58
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Colin McIntosh and Maurice Joseph led a balanced attack with 17 points each as Vermont defeated Yale 89-58 Tuesday night. McIntosh scored 12 of his points during a 20-3 run that stretched a 22-18 lead to 42-21. Mike Trimboli had 16 points and 7 assists for Vermont. Yale pulled within 51-37 with 15:25 to go, but the Catamounts (1-1) scored the next seven to push it back to 21. Another 13-2 run boosted the lead to 30. Ross Morin had 13 points and Garrett Fiddler 11 points for the Bulldogs (0-2). Vermont shot 53 percent from the field, hitting 35 of 65 field goal attempts while Yale shot 21 of 47. The Catamounts also outrebounded the Bulldogs, 37-23, with McIntosh hauling in 8.
